//! 2. `<directory>/<data_object>` if `file` is absent
//! 3. `./<file>` if `directory` is absent but `file` is present
//! 4. `./<data_object>` if neither `directory` nor `file` is present
//!
//! The destination directory must already exist — baton-rs
//! follows upstream baton in not auto-creating destinations.
//!
//! Optional per-record decoration: each output record can be
//! enriched with the same metadata fields `baton-list` exposes
//! (`--avu` / `--acl` / `--size` / `--checksum` / `--replicate` /
//! `--timestamp`). Decoration runs after the get itself via the
//! shared `operations::metaquery::decorate_result` helper. Errored
//! get results are passed through without decoration so the
//! original error isn't masked.

